    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 76 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from"
                            >Truman</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d76fn1">Presumably sent to the United States Naval Attaché,
                        London, via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-18">18 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. The press reports referred to in your 93<note n="2" xml:id="d76fn2">
                        <ref target="#d72">document No. 72</ref>.</note> are not authentic.</p>
                <p>I shall keep the promise made to you by President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName> if conditions at the time make it practicable.</p>
                <pb facs="0240" n="108" xml:id="pg_108"/>
                <p>May I express a hope that the contents of this message will not get into the
                    papers.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
